textAfterTable: 12 Songs Biography Genre: Pop Years Active: '90s Yölintu are a Finnish schlager band that broke through to mainstream success in 1998 and released a long line of Top Five albums from that point onward. Founded in 1992, the band is comprised of Simo Silmu (vocals), Matti Silmu (guitar), Markus Kuusijoensuu (guitar), Kari Heiskari (bass), and Mikko Taipale (drums). Saku Mansikkamäki, a founding member, was the band's drummer for over a decade (1992-2003). Yölintu made their album debut in 1993 with Yölintu Laskeutuu, followed by Pieni Lintunen (1994)...
